Author-Name: Thomas Philippon  
Author-Name: Vasiliki Skreta  
Title: Optimal Interventions in Markets with Adverse Selection 
Abstract:
 We study the design of interventions to stabilize financial markets
 plagued by adverse selection. Our contribution is to analyze the
 information revealed by participation decisions. Taking part in  a
 government program carries a stigma, and outside options are mechanism
 dependent. We show that the efficiency of an intervention can be assessed
 by its impact on the market interest rate. The presence of an outside
 market determines the nature of optimal interventions and the choice of
 financial instruments (debt guarantees in our model), but it does not
 affect implementation costs. (JEL D82, D86, G01, G20, G31)
