Author-Name: Jaromir B. Nosal  
Title: Understanding International Prices: Customers as Capital 
Abstract:
 The article develops a new theory of pricing to market driven by dynamic
 frictions of building market shares. Our key innovation is a capital
 theoretic model of marketing in which relations with customers are
 valuable. We discipline the introduced friction using data on differences
 between short-run and long-run price elasticity of international  trade
 flows. We show that the model accounts for several pricing "puzzles" of
 international macroeconomics. (JEL E13, F14, F31, F41, F44, M31)
