Title: Contracts versus Salaries in Matching 
Abstract:
 Firms and workers may sign complex contracts that govern many aspects of
 their interactions. I show that when firms regard contracts as
 substitutes, bargaining over contracts can be understood as bargaining
 only over wages. Substitutes is the assumption commonly used to guarantee
 the existence of stable matchings of workers and firms. (JEL C78, D86,
 J31, J41)
